-- Queen Elizabeth II to Miss Commonwealth Meeting in Sri Lanka
-- B y   K i t t y   D o n a l d s o n
-- 2013-05-07T07:50:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-07/queen-elizabeth-ii-to-miss-commonwealth-meeting-in-sri-lanka.html
Queen Elizabeth II , the U.K. monarch
who is also head of the 54 nations of the Commonwealth, will not
attend its meeting in Sri Lanka later this year and will instead
send her heir, Prince Charles, her office said today.  Commonwealth leaders meet every two years to discuss global
and Commonwealth issues, and to agree on collective policies and
initiatives in a grouping that represents more than 2 billion
people. The  meeting this year  will be held in Colombo from Nov.
15 to Nov. 17.  “The queen will be represented at this year’s Commonwealth
heads of government meeting by the Prince of  Wales ,”  Buckingham
Palace  said in an e-mailed statement, referring to Charles by
his official title. The queen is age 87.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kitty Donaldson in London at 
